   it is a good approximation to a rational agent's behavior as the number
   of agents increases. Formally, if every agent except one follows the MFE
   strategy, then the remaining agent's loss on playing the MFE strategy
   converges to zero as the number of agents in the market increases. We
   conclude by discussing the implications of the auction format and design
   on the auctioneer's revenue. In particular, we establish the revenue
   equivalence of standard auctions in dynamic mean field settings, and
   discuss optimal selection of reserve prices in dynamic auctions.
