   taxes, for instance) are much more effective in reducing carbon
   emissions, whereas battery-price-reducing policy interventions are more
   effective for reducing oil dependence. Taken together, our results help
   a policy maker identify the superior system for achieving the desired
   objectives. They also highlight that policy makers should not conflate
   the dual objectives of oil dependence and emissions reductions as the
   preferred system, and the policy interventions that further that system
