   statements in two ways. First, we show the following analytical result:
   when demand is composed of a base demand random component plus a surge
   demand random component, which occurs with a certain small probability,
   the best TBS policy is close to optimal (over all policies) in a
   well-defined sense. Second, we also numerically investigate the cost
   effectiveness of the best TBS policy on a test bed of problem instances.
